ATTR: condition: good#cylinders: 4 cylinders#drive: 4wd#fuel: gas#odometer: 130000#paint color: red#title status: clean#transmission: manual#type: hatchback
MESSAGE: im looking to sell my daily driver so i can replace it with a truck. odometer just turned 130k and is getting used a little more every week. mobile 1 full synthetic oil every 3k miles with napa gold filter and chevron 91 every fill up. everything works as it should aside from the ac. ac system is complete and cold when charged but leaks out the refrigerant so some seal or o-ring or hose needs replacing...if i own much longer i will be fixing this issue. black leather heated seats. 5 speed manual transmission shifts perfectly. timing belt has been done; fog lights work; ej255 turbocharged engine is stock and pulls hard; doesnt skip a beat. the only aftermarket parts are the stance brand coilovers (link featured below); a jdm wrx hood scoop that is taller than stock; and the jdm dash gauge cluster which all work (oil temp; boost; volts). the coilovers are fully height and dampening adjustable and have less than 15k miles on them. comes with 17in konig wheels plastidipped flat black with tons of tread left on the tires. it has a kenwood deck with bluetooth microphone and 10in sub set up out of the way in the hatch. mechanically this car is sound and has many miles left in her. would be a very cool car to modify but i need to keep it reliable for carrying kids around. cosmetically the car isnt bad. the paint cleans up nice. has a normal amount of dings and dents but nothing horrible. the hood shows swirl marks. i have high quality body shop matched color paint that can go with the car if youre handy like that. i bought it to do the scoop and it turned out great until i wet sanded it a little too deep. finding an xt with a clean title and not crazy high miles is getting harder to do. this is a good one; dont miss out. im pretty firm at $11k but cash talks. not really interested in trades but i guess send me your offers and worst i can say is no! i bought this car with around 115k miles so i havent put too many on it but i have babied it since ive owned it. never riced; raced; or red-lined and honestly ive gone overboard and did oil changed a little too often. please email your contact info and i will get back to you asap. i can text more pictures. it seems when i leave a contact number on cl i get texts at 3am asking if ill trade for a playstation so if youre seriously interested send an email and ill check it often. im in no hurry to sell this car and am daily driving it until the right buyer comes. thanks for looking!#ps- the shown pictures are old. the one showing the dash shows the oem cd player not the new one. the lower pic shows the car before it was tinted (fronts i believe are 20% and all rears are blacked out) and the first picture was recently taken but shes filthy! better pics to come#coilovers- these are the ss model. height; dampening; and camber adjustable on all 4. 6k/6k spring rate. these ride nice and are not bouncy. you can lay down and adjust the dampening in a few seconds. stance has since replaced these with the xr1 model but here is their description:#http://www.shopstance.com/stance-xr1-coilovers-for-subaru-forester-02-07/#i listed once before but had email issues with a phone update. my email is working fine now.

TITLE: 2006 subaru forester 2.5x ll bean edition (fully restored); reduced!
ATTR: condition: good#cylinders: 4 cylinders#drive: 4wd#fuel: gas#odometer: 207000#paint color: green#size: mid-size#title status: clean#transmission: automatic#type: wagon
MESSAGE: were selling our very clean; almost fully-restored 2006 subaru forester 2.5x ll bean edition - in great shape! (surprisingly great shape...)#we originally listed this for $9;500 but since we need to sell we are asking $8;000 or taking the best offer. (i encourage you to read how we have almost fully restored this car before judging it purely on its mileage.)#i probably dont need to tell you; but this is the ultimate northwest car. during the snowiest winter in years; we were driving around with confidence and never slipped once. nothing beats having that confidence of 4wd and the low center of gravity of a subaru in the snow; rain; or ice.#this car is a pleasure to drive! extremely zippy and handles excellently. very comfortable ride - great for road trips. excellent gas mileage on the streets and highway. big gas tank keep stops at the pump to a minimum.#the ll bean has all the bells and whistles you want - full sunroof; auto windows; seat warmers; leather seats; auto lights; wood steering wheel; cruise control; etc etc. its fully loaded.#we added a very nice pioneer stereo that has bluetooth calling installed (and bluetooth media); aux/ipod functions; and a single cd player. its the one upgrade that was really needed and makes this car so much more awesome.#this car has a lot of miles on it but we have poured well over $5k of work into it to make it last another 100k miles and/or 7-8 years without major engine repairs.#new parts: head gaskets; drive belt; timing belt; steering rack; front struts; catalytic convertor; battery; tires (over 35;000 miles left); and more... much of which comes with a warrantee from the reputable green drop garage. all work history is verifiable.#this car is ready to go! basically; almost every 200;000 mile repair that has needed to be done; has been done. this car is going to last a long time with only minor repairs going forward.#the only reason we are selling this car is that we are moving to sunny california and we already have another 4x4 so we dont need this one anymore. we need a small prius.#fact is; youd be hard pressed to find any subaru for sale for under $10;000; period. this one is (almost) fully restored; has all the bells and whistles; has never had any bodywork; has very few scratches/small dents; no rust; clean title; and has just had over $5;000 work of work poured into it by a reputable garage. the majority of the work has been completed in the last year and within the last 5;000 miles. and yes; like any car with 200k miles; it has some wear and tear; but the car is shockingly clean and in amazing shape. everything works. no broken knobs; switches; etc. its just been well-taken care of.#one more thing: it also comes with about $400 left on a limited warrantee that will expire later this year. you may not use it but it does transfer to you with the car.#youre just not going to find an ll bean with the ability to run another 100k with minimal repairs for under 10k... we know at this price this wont last long but we are pricing it low because we need to sell it before we move. so if this is the subi youve been looking for; and youve got the cash; send us an email so we can show it to you and let you drive it around a bit. maybe it will be your safe; reliable and fun car for the next 5-10 years!#-julia and david

MESSAGE: this 2009 subaru foresters wires were attacked by pack rats.  took it to the dealer in tucson.  they replaced the wiring to the fuel pump.  when we got it home we discovered a fuel leak and had it towed back to the dealer.  they found the pack rats had attacked the fuel line as well.  the fuel had soaked the liner beneath the back seat and it seeped into the foam.  the dealer replaced the fuel lines and the foam.  they suggested a lot more work needed to be done to the car.  on the way from the dealer we decided to have the oil changed.  the car died in front of jiffy lube and would not start again.  we had it towed to a friends house who is a backyard mechanic so he could work on it.#he found the timing belt had jumped a position.  he replaced:#timing belt and all pulleys#oil pump#water pump#all other belts#the car would still not start.  he thought the head gasket would need to be changed.  the water temp light flashes between red and blue.#if you know how to fix this car it can be yours for $5;000.00

MESSAGE: nice extremely reliable 01 subaru forester 5spd manual. from trips across the country to weekends exploring colorado back roads; this forester has never failed to start or let me down. i am only selling because i am buying a van to live in for the next few months in california.#it has 190k on the odometer; the engine was replaced just before i bought the car at approximately 160k with an engine with approximately 120k. i purchased the vehicle from auto associates (affiliate shop of allroos); a long time subaru specialist in evergreen and aurora. along with the engine; the timing belt; water pump; and clutch were replaced. has had oil changed every 3k miles since.#mechanically this car is in great condition. just had my mechanic do a  thorough check before putting it up for sale; it came back with a clean bill of health save for a few items:#it has had the check engine light on since i bought the car; its a po420 code; which is for the o2 sensor; if you google this you will find that its a common problem with this era of foresters. i replaced front and rear o2 sensors just to be safe; but it made no difference. the shop i bought it from; my regular mechanic; and another trusted mechanic; as well as the internet; all said the same thing; that it is a common problem and simply a phantom code caused by the tight tolerances of the ecu; and a waste of time and money to pursue fixing (gets normal fuel economy and passed emissions no problem - if you clear the code the light typically stays off for a couple days)#it needs a new passenger cv boot - getting replaced before selling.#the tires will need to be replaced soon; my plan before deciding to sell was to get through the summer and get a set of good all season tires (id recommend yokohama avid envigors) before winter.#cosmetically in fair condition. the hood and front and rear of roof are painted with plastic-dip. the clear coat was beginning to peal when i bought it; and didnt want it to worsen; and i liked the look of the black accents. it can be easily pealed off without damage to the paint if you dont like it. has some stains on the upholstery; but no tears and still very comfortable. windshield is brand new; along with passenger side turn signal light. headlights just polished. interior freshly shampooed. never smoked in.#if you arent already sold on a forester as your next vehicle; know there is a reason they are all over the sprouts and whole foods parking lots of colorado. they do great in the snow; have good clearance and traction for getting down most 4wd roads; can swallow tons of gear  friends; and are bulletproof.#$4750 obo. open to trades if you have a van that will suit my needs.#available to show most mornings and early afternoons or after 10pm. typically commute to boulder in the evenings; can make arrangements to show it there as well. calling or texting is best; i dont always get to my email right away. thanks! travis

MESSAGE: 04 xt 180;000 miles. runs and drives great. driven daily to work 30 min both ways. i recently moved here from ohio and the car got me here 1;400 miles with zero issues 26 hours straight. the engine is nearly 100% stock apart from the oil and boost sensors. i just changed the oil and checked everything out about 10 minutes ago. oil is changed in this car every 3000-4000 miles with full synthetic every time. i take great care of my cars and i think it shows. the only reason that i am looking to get rid of it is to get into something rwd again.##@i will talk about trades at the end@##-timing belt and water pump were professionally done at 176;645 miles. (pictured)#-a/c works great after a little work on the compressor clutch. everyone always says cold a/c but i never see anyone put a thermometer in a vent. so i did. (pictured) the clutch still disengages every now and then but only for a few seconds. if you are really concerned; a new clutch is about $50. ill even show you how to change it if you want. it is really simple.#-engine; trans and clutch all feel great in this car#-brakes are a little soft but have never let me down. the car came to me with the rear disc brakes upgraded to the larger diameter h6 brakes. meaning that the brakes on the rear are from another subaru that came with the 6 cylinder engine.#-meagan street coil overs that i bought used and did some work to free them up. they are now easily adjusted to the ride height of your choosing thanks to some anti seize.#-aftermarket oil pressure; oil temp and boost sensors (gauges in the dash)#-aftermarket bluetooth radio adapter called transit blu. tucks in the dash and lets you play music from your phone with no ugly wires or fm transmitter. i got it to keep the stock look but to have the convenience of bluetooth. the on/off switch to the left of the steering wheel is for this. sometimes you have to shut it off and power it back on to get it to work. this only happens 1 out of 20 times.#-inno bike rack#-ambit wheels#-tires and alignment have 4000 miles on them##-cons#-check engine light is on for a bank 1 lean code. this normally means a vacuum leak or a bad maf. i looked for a couple of days for leaks; changed some hoses and found nothing so i cleaned the maf; cleared the codes and then set off for my oh to tx move. i drove 4 hours with a cleaned maf before the light came back on. for this reason i think i have a maf that is going bad. these are about $130 and again ill show you how to change it.#-battery is corroding a bit but turns over strong every time#-body is dent free and has only these 3 flaws------#-1 small spot of rust (pictured) the car is from ohio so it is hard to avoid.#-1 scratch on the drivers side front fender from my old neighbors kids.#-the roof bar ends clear coat is pealing (pictured) but no painted clear coat is.##trades - if you have a manual 350z; g35; or g37 let me know. i will take a look. other than those; i will look at 300hp rwd cars but i will not accept any auto transmissions; or fwd cars.#sorry for the long ad but i like to avoid answering the same questions over and over.#call or text steve after 5pm mon-fri. after noon on weekends - (three30) three40 three121#if you are interested i can meet at 1604 and culebra at one of the fast food places.
